{"article_id":"6wH9XsRSJ7PBexyD","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"A majority of justices on the Supreme Court seemed ready to affirm President Donald Trump ' s decision","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"to rescind the Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"( DACA )","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"program , an amnesty initiative","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"that shields illegal aliens from deportation","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"if they entered the country as children .","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"A coalition of state entities and civil rights groups convinced lower courts to stop DACA ' s termination ,","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"arguing","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"the government has not sufficiently justified its decision","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"to terminate the program .","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"Neither the lower courts nor the challengers contend","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"Trump lacks the fundamental power","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"to end DACA .","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"The crux of the dispute is whether the administration followed the law","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"as it wound-down the program ,","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"and if the decision can be reviewed in court in the first place .","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"A closely divided Supreme Court seemed inclined to uphold President Donald Trump ' s bid","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"to terminate the Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"( DACA )","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"program during arguments Tuesday morning .","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"The high court ' s conservative majority appeared to think","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"the administration has provided an adequate basis","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"for ending the policy ,","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"and in spaces even wondered","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"if the courts have power","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"to review the dispute .","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"Chief Justice John Roberts noted","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"that the high court in 2016 affirmed a decision of the 5th U.S . Circuit Court of Appeals","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"that blocked an Obama-era amnesty program","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"called Deferred Action for Parents of Americans","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"( DAPA ) .","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"The 5th Circuit ' s ruling and the Supreme Court ' s subsequent affirmance provide a sufficient rationale","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"for ending DACA ,","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"which is largely similar to DAPA ,","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"Roberts suggested .","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"\" You ' ve got a court of appeals decision","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"affirmed by an equally-divided Supreme Court , \"","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"Roberts said , in reference to the earlier DAPA case .","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"\" Can ' t he just say","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"that ' s the basis","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"on which I ' m making this decision ? \"","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"Apart from concerns about DACA ' s legality , Justice Brett Kavanaugh said","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"the Department of Homeland Security","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"( DHS )","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"identified independent policy reasons","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"for ending the program .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"He repeatedly challenged lawyers","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"representing left-leaning states and civil rights groups","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"to describe why the government ' s explanation for its decision fell short .","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"( RELATED :","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"American Hero Fights Traffic Stop All The Way To The Supreme Court )","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"DACA does not confer lawful status on recipients ,","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"nor is it a defense against deportation .","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"Instead , if delays removal for a renewable two-year period","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"and allows beneficiaries to apply for work permits .","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"Former President Barack Obama established the program in 2012 .","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"To qualify ,","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"recipients must have entered the country unlawfully before age 16 ,","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"show five years of continuous residence in the U.S. ,","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"graduate high school ,","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"serve in the Armed Forces ,","depth":14},{"id":61,"text":"or enroll in school .","depth":14},{"id":62,"text":"DHS oversees the DACA program .","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"There are approximately 700,000 so-called \" Dreamers \" as of this writing .","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"California is home to the largest number of DACA beneficiaries","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"according to U.S. Citizen and Immigration Services","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"( USCIS ) ,","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"with approximately 190,000 recipients .","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"Texas follows at about 110,000 .","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"Though initially established as a stopgap measure ,","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"the policy enjoys broad , bipartisan support .","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"The president has repeatedly expressed reluctance to end DACA .","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"Yet a decision from the high court","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"authorizing its termination","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"would give Trump significant leverage in negotiations with Congress over an immigration deal .","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"Trump alluded to such an outcome in a September tweet .","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"DACA will be going before the Supreme Court .","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"It is a document","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"that even President Obama didn ' t feel","depth":14},{"id":79,"text":"he had the legal right","depth":14},{"id":80,"text":"to sign","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"- he signed it anyway !","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"Rest assured","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"if the SC does","depth":14},{"id":85,"text":"what all say","depth":15},{"id":86,"text":"it must ,","depth":15},{"id":87,"text":"based on the law ,","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"a bipartisan deal will be made to the benefit of all !","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"- Donald J. Trump","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"( @ realDonaldTrump )","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"September 6 , 2019","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"Acting Homeland Security Secretary Elaine Duke set a timeline for DACA ' s termination in September 2017 .","depth":6},{"id":93,"text":"In a memo","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"explaining her decision ,","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"Duke said","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"then-Attorney General Jeff Sessions told DHS","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"that the program is unlawful .","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"She further noted","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"that a coalition of states was threatening to sue the federal government over DACA in view of the 5th Circuit ' s DAPA decision .","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"Duke ' s memo prompted a flurry of litigation .","depth":6},{"id":101,"text":"Federal trial judges in California , New York , and Washington , D.C. , blocked the order on a nationwide basis .","depth":6},{"id":102,"text":"Neither the plaintiffs nor the lower courts believe","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"Trump lacks the power","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"to terminate DACA .","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"Instead , the challengers say","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"Duke ' s memo is \" arbitrary and capricious \" under the Administrative Procedure Act","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"( APA )","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"and must be set aside .","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"The APA requires","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"that the government provide clear , reasoned explanations for new policy .","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"The plaintiffs argue","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"Duke ' s memo is a \" superficial explanation \"","depth":13},{"id":113,"text":"that \" fails to explain the Acting Secretary ' s reasoning , \"","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"and thus violates the APA .","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"The challengers say","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"a second memo","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"former Homeland Security Secretary Kirstjen Nielsen","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"issued on DACA ' s termination in June 2018","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"is similarly deficient .","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"\" It is truly remarkable that a Cabinet-level officer would offer such a cursory explanation for a decision","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"that affects hundreds of thousands of lives","depth":13},{"id":122,"text":"and reverses a longstanding and carefully-reasoned government position , \"","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"the plaintiffs told the high court in legal briefs .","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"\" The APA requires more . \"","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"The Trump administration argues","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"its decision","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"to cancel DACA","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"is not subject to APA arbitrary and capricious review in court .","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"That ' s because the APA doesn ' t apply to actions","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"\" committed to agency discretion by law. \"","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"Rescinding a non-enforcement policy like DACA is a \" quintessential \" example of agency discretion ,","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"the government said in legal filings ,","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"much like a prosecutor ' s decision","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"to pursue or decline indictments .","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"The government ' s discretion is especially powerful in the immigration area ,","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"the administration adds .","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"Justice Samuel Alito seemed to agree with those propositions .","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"He compared the DACA dispute to a case","depth":10},{"id":139,"text":"involving a hypothetical Justice Department decision","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"not to prosecute cases of cocaine possession below certain amounts .","depth":11},{"id":141,"text":"Ted Olson , a lawyer","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"challenging DACA ' s termination ,","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"agreed","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"Alito ' s cocaine example could not be challenged in court .","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"\" Well , what ' s the difference ? \"","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"Alito shot back .","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"Justice Neil Gorsuch expressed similar doubts .","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"Even if its decision can be reviewed in court ,","depth":10},{"id":149,"text":"the administration says","depth":11},{"id":150,"text":"the Duke and Nielsen memos give ample grounds","depth":13},{"id":151,"text":"for ending DACA","depth":13},{"id":152,"text":"that the courts must accept .","depth":12},{"id":153,"text":"The left-leaning justices were particularly dubious of that claim ,","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"saying","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"those materials did not address real-world consequences in a meaningful way .","depth":11},{"id":156,"text":"Justice Sonia Sotomayor pointedly accused the government of blaming the law","depth":12},{"id":157,"text":"to dodge political heat .","depth":12},{"id":158,"text":"\" There ' s a whole lot of reliance interests","depth":15},{"id":159,"text":"that weren ' t looked at ,","depth":15},{"id":160,"text":"including the current president","depth":16},{"id":161,"text":"telling DACA-eligible people","depth":17},{"id":162,"text":"that they were safe under him","depth":18},{"id":163,"text":"and that he would find a way","depth":19},{"id":164,"text":"to keep them here , \"","depth":19},{"id":165,"text":"Sotomayor told Solicitor General Noel Francisco .","depth":15},{"id":166,"text":"\" Where is all of this really considered and weighed ? \"","depth":14},{"id":167,"text":"she added .","depth":14},{"id":168,"text":"\" Where is the political decision made clearly ,","depth":14},{"id":169,"text":"that this is not about the law ,","depth":15},{"id":170,"text":"this is about our choice","depth":16},{"id":171,"text":"to destroy lives . \"","depth":16},{"id":172,"text":"\" We own this , \"","depth":14},{"id":173,"text":"Francisco said in reply .","depth":14},{"id":174,"text":"( RELATED :","depth":11},{"id":175,"text":"Supreme Court Hears Aaaarguments Over Blackbeard ' s Pirate Wreck )","depth":11},{"id":176,"text":"Justice Stephen Breyer referenced numerous amicus","depth":10},{"id":177,"text":"( or \" friend of the court \" )","depth":10},{"id":178,"text":"briefs from businesses , labor unions , and religious organizations","depth":9},{"id":179,"text":"describing the benefits","depth":9},{"id":180,"text":"DACA recipients provide their organizations .","depth":9},{"id":181,"text":"Breyer said","depth":9},{"id":182,"text":"the Duke and Nielsen documents didn ' t seem \" to take into account that broad range of interests . \"","depth":9},{"id":183,"text":"\" There are 66 healthcare organizations , \"","depth":10},{"id":184,"text":"Breyer told Francisco .","depth":10},{"id":185,"text":"\" There are three labor unions .","depth":10},{"id":186,"text":"There are 210 educational associations .","depth":11},{"id":187,"text":"There are six military organizations .","depth":12},{"id":188,"text":"There are three home builders , five states plus those involved , 108 ,","depth":14},{"id":189,"text":"I think ,","depth":14},{"id":190,"text":"municipalities and cities , 129 religious organizations , and 145 businesses . \"","depth":13},{"id":191,"text":"Though Gorsuch was broadly sympathetic to the administration ,","depth":6},{"id":192,"text":"at one point he telegraphed a possible compromise .","depth":6},{"id":193,"text":"He asked Francisco","depth":7},{"id":194,"text":"if the justices should send the case back to the lower courts","depth":8},{"id":195,"text":"and give the administration a chance","depth":9},{"id":196,"text":"to offer a more detailed rationale for its decision .","depth":9},{"id":197,"text":"\" Given the extent of the reliance interests and the size of the class ,","depth":9},{"id":198,"text":"more needed to be said ,","depth":9},{"id":199,"text":"more could be said ,","depth":9},{"id":200,"text":"and it wouldn ' t be a huge burden to require the government on remand to say more , \"","depth":9},{"id":201,"text":"Gorsuch said ,","depth":8},{"id":202,"text":"summarizing the plaintiffs ' s views .","depth":8},{"id":203,"text":"Kavanaugh countered","depth":6},{"id":204,"text":"that a federal trial court in Washington , D.C. did just that at an earlier phase of the litigation .","depth":6},{"id":205,"text":"Nielsen produced her June 2018 memo at the direction of U.S. District Judge John Bates ,","depth":7},{"id":206,"text":"who found the Duke ' s directive wanting .","depth":7},{"id":207,"text":"As such , Kavanaugh questioned the value of an additional remand .","depth":6},{"id":208,"text":"The Mexican government and a coalition of big businesses are urging the justices to maintain DACA .","depth":2},{"id":209,"text":"A decision in Tuesday ' s dispute , No . 18-587 Department of Homeland Security v. Regents of the University of California and the consolidated cases , is expected by June 2020 .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":419,"left":417,"right":418,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":417,"left":301,"right":416,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":301,"left":225,"right":300,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":225,"left":215,"right":224,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":215,"left":0,"right":214,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":214,"left":212,"right":213,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":212,"left":211,"right":3,"relation":"same-unit","nuclear